rooms.Name: The entrance to the county Hospital.
rooms.Description:
You are standing in front of the information desk at the county hospital.
There are several people in line in front of you.  You wonder how this
hospital stays in business with such inefficent employees.

rooms.Name: In the hall of the county hospital.
rooms.Description:
There are rooms on either side of this hall way and on each door there are 
the names of the patients in that particular room.  The floors are done
in an industrial looking white and grey fleck tile.  The walls are painted
with a sanitary white.  There are nurses and doctors running about the 
halls seeing to their patients.  Above you the fluorescent lights hum
and flicker with the effects of a good lullaby, making you very sleepy.
There is an antiseptic smell in here that goes along with all hospitals.
You can hear the Doctors being paged and the patients ringing their nurses.
You wonder if somewhere around here if there isn't someone to help you.

rooms.Name: In the hall of the county hospital.
rooms.Description:
This is pretty much like the rest of the Hospital halls except that there is
a guard here and there is a locked door to the west.  You wonder what is 
behind the door til you see on the door there is a sign which says
mental ward.

Exits.Description: There is a door here leading to the mental ward of county hospital.

ExtraDescs.Description:
The sign on the door says "County Hospital Mental Ward."
                          " Please sign in"

rooms.Name: In a standard hospital room.
rooms.Description:
This is your ordinary hospital room.  There is the usuall adjustable bed and
T.V. that has been bolted to the wall.... like you would actually steal the
crappy things.  The walls are the same white as the halls and the floors 
are the same industrial tiles.  The only difference in here is that the 
smell is stronger in here. The patient must get well pretty quickly here
cause they wouldn't want to stay in this gloomy room any longer than they 
have to.
